Automatic transforming of a categorical variable according to a new encoding

cat2cat.Rd

Automatic transforming of a categorical variable according to a new encoding

cat2cat(
  data = list(old = NULL, new = NULL, cat_var = NULL, id_var = NULL, time_var = NULL,
    multipier_var = NULL, freqs_df = NULL),
  mappings = list(trans = NULL, direction = NULL),
  ml = list(method = NULL, features = NULL, args = NULL)
)

Arguments

data

list with 4, 5 or 6 named fileds `old` `new` `cat_var` `time_var` and optional `id_var`,`multipier_var`,`freq_df`
mappings

list with 2 named fileds `trans` `direction`
ml

list with 3 named fields `method` `features` `args``

Value

list of 2 data.frames

Details

data args

  • "old" data.frame

  • "new" data.frame

  • "id_var" name of the id variable

  • "cat_var" name of the caterogical variable

  • "time_var" name of the time varaiable

  • "multipier_var" name of the multipier variable - number of replication needed to reproduce the population

  • "freqs_df" data.frame with 2 columns where first one is category name and second counts which will be used to assess the probabilities.

mappings args

  • "trans" data.frame with 2 columns - transition table

  • "direction" direction - "backward or "forward"

ml args

  • "method" character "knn"

  • "features" vector of features names

  • "args" k number of k nearest n

Examples

data(occup)
data(trans)

occup_old <- occup[occup$year == 2008, ]
occup_new <- occup[occup$year == 2010, ]

cat2cat(
  data = list(old = occup_old, new = occup_new, cat_var = "code", time_var = "year"),
  mappings = list(trans = trans, direction = "forward")
)

cat2cat(
  data = list(old = occup_old, new = occup_new, cat_var = "code", time_var = "year"),
  mappings = list(trans = trans, direction = "forward"),
  ml = list(
    method = "knn",
    features = c("age", "sex", "edu", "exp", "parttime", "salary"),
    args = list(k = 10)
  )
)
